==English==

=== Pronunciation ===
\Pre*ven"tion\
=== Etymology ===
[[Cf.]] [[F.]] '' pr['e]vention''

[[prevent]] + [[-tion]]
=== Noun ===
'''prevention'''
the act of obstructing, hindering or slowing an action.
# The act of going, or state of being, before. ([[Obs.]])

 The greater the distance, the greater the prevention. --[[w:Bacon|Bacon]].

# [[Anticipation]]; esp., anticipation of needs, wishes, [[hazard]]s and [[risk]]s ; hence, [[precaution]]; forethought. [Obs.] --Hammond. Shak.

# The act of [[preventing]] or [[hindering]]; [[obstruction]] of action,  access, or approach; thwarting. --South.
 Casca, be sudden, for we fear prevention. --[[w:Shak|Shak]].

